channel.title: Receiving A item From Clicking a object z508 palidino's base
channel.description:
Today i will be showing you how to recive a item from clicking a object
diffculty 2/10 if you follow my steps =)
files we are going to be useing ObjectOption1.java command prompt (the one you use to run server) and a 525 item id list witch can be downloaded from http://www.mediafire.com/?d2ujyuz2kz1 this is for codes for items you whant to add = ) also you will need jdk if you do not have the link is http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/widget/jdk6.jsp
the first thing you will whant to do is find what object you would like to recive the item our show a interface i'll show you the one i will be useing [IMG]http://i39.tinypic.com/4uh2zs.png[/img]
now click the object and you should receive a message in your command prompt saying unhandled object 1: 17320 (the number is diffrent for each object) i'll show you pic i got [IMG]http://i39.tinypic.com/286xz4g.png[/img] now we have the object id code you will be useing find the file ObjectOption1.java if you do not know where it is open your server folder src>net>com>codeusa>net>packethandler>ObjectOption1.java open it and scroll down till you see the case section now right one in saying
case 17320: (this is code I received in my cmd so put yours in) Engine.playerItems.addItem(p, 4708, 1); (p, ITEMID, AMT);What this does is add the ITEMID and AMT (amount) to the players inventory break; [IMG]http://i41.tinypic.com/jql5e0.png[/img]
save the files compact and it should work if it does not leave a reply and i will try and help you if you want any more tutorials leave a message =) [IMG]http://i43.tinypic.com/ea2wk6.png[/img]
